solutions.content:
Sliding window. 

`i` is left, `j` is right, `n` is the sum of the current window. Keep moving `j` to the right, adding in whatever value we hit to our sum. 

If the total window size hits the limit, pull up the left hand side of the window and drop the value at that index from our sum. Then set this sum into the correct index - just before the start of the window if `k` is positive, and just after the end of the window if `k` is negative.
```
vector<int> decrypt(vector<int>& code, int k) {
	vector<int> v(code.size());
	for (int i = 0, j = 0, n = 0; i < code.size() && k; ++j) {
		n += code[j % code.size()];
		if (j - i == abs(k)) v[k > 0 ? i - 1 : (j + 1) % code.size()] = n -= code[i++];
	}
	return v;
}
```

