# Intuition
Generate the array just the way it is described in the problem description.

# Approach
Create an array of the same size, as all operations are done simultaneously, which means we should not edit the original array.

For every index in the array, we sum all the values that we need. 

steps: the amount of steps we make. We have to make a total of abs(k) steps.
index: The index of the value we add to sum. We have code to wrap it around if it goes beyond the array bounds.
sum: Sum of the values.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> decrypt(vector<int>& code, int k) {
        int n = code.size();

        vector<int> ans(n, 0);

        for(int i = 0; i < code.size(); ++i) {
            int steps = 0;
            int index = i;
            int sum = 0;
            while(steps < abs(k)) {
                index += (k > 0) ? 1 : -1;
                if(index >= n) {
                    index = 0;
                } else if(index < 0) {
                    index = n - 1;
                }

                sum += code[index];
                ++steps;
            }

            ans[i] = sum;
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```

