solutions.content:
The idea here is to simply push 'b' onto a Stack whenever we encounter it.
But what if we encounter 'a', in this case we check if there is a 'b' present already only then we pop 'b' from the Stack (which signifies a Delete operation).
```
class Solution {
    public int minimumDeletions(String s) {
        int count = 0;
        Stack<Character> balance = new Stack();
        char c = ' ';
        for(int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)
        {
            c = s.charAt(i);
            if(!balance.empty() && (balance.peek() == 'b' && c == 'a'))
            {
                balance.pop();
                count++;
            }
            else if(c == 'b')
                balance.push(c);
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```
