solutions.content:
Any time if we see an 'a' we need to make a decision whether we: 
- delete that 'a'
- or delete all the previous 'b's

we calculate the deletion count for that 'a' depending on which is least expensive - if the number of 'b's before this 'a' is greater than the deletion count after deleting this 'a' (i.e. +1 to the previous deletion count), then it makes sense NOT to delete all the previous 'b's because it would prove to be costlier than deleting this 'a'.

Simliarly, if the number of 'b's is lesser than the count of deletion after deleting this 'a', we are better off deleting all the previous 'b's

```
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumDeletions(string s) {
        int bCountSoFar = 0, deleteCount = 0;
        for (char ch: s) {
//             at any point if we see 'a', we either delete it or delete all previous 'b's depending on which is less expensive
            if (ch == 'a') {
//                 if number of 'b's so far is greater, then delete this 'a'
                if(bCountSoFar > deleteCount + 1)
                    deleteCount++;
//                 or else we delete the previous 'b's
                else deleteCount = bCountSoFar;
            }
            // keep counting the number of 'b's
            else if (ch == 'b') ++bCountSoFar;
        }
        return deleteCount;
    }
};
```

